cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the development of deep learning architectures and optimizers, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on data collection and selection also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of data mining (cs.DM). However, given the emphasis on supervised learning and deep learning, the first five sub-categories are more likely to be relevant.
